33 // Setup for Windows DLL export/import. When building the V8 DLL the
34 // BUILDING_V8_SHARED needs to be defined. When building a program which uses
35 // the V8 DLL USING_V8_SHARED needs to be defined. When either building the V8
36 // static library or building a program which uses the V8 static library neither
37 // BUILDING_V8_SHARED nor USING_V8_SHARED should be defined.
38 #ifdef BUILDING_V8_SHARED
39 # define V8_EXPORT __declspec(dllexport)
40 #elif USING_V8_SHARED
41 # define V8_EXPORT __declspec(dllimport)
42 #else
43 # define V8_EXPORT
44 #endif // BUILDING_V8_SHARED
45 
46 #else // V8_OS_WIN
47 
48 // Setup for Linux shared library export.
49 #if V8_HAS_ATTRIBUTE_VISIBILITY
50 # ifdef BUILDING_V8_SHARED
51 # define V8_EXPORT __attribute__ ((visibility("default")))
52 # else
53 # define V8_EXPORT
54 # endif
55 #else
56 # define V8_EXPORT
57 #endif
58 
59 #endif // V8_OS_WIN

165 #define TYPE_CHECK(T, S) \
166  while (false) { \
167  *(static_cast<T* volatile*>(0)) = static_cast<S*>(0); \
168  }

201 template <class T>
202 class Local {
203  public:
204  V8_INLINE Local() : val_(0) {}
205  template <class S>
206  V8_INLINE Local(Local<S> that)
207  : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
213  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
214  }
215 
219  V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == 0; }
220 
224  V8_INLINE void Clear() { val_ = 0; }
225 
226  V8_INLINE T* operator->() const { return val_; }
227 
228  V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return val_; }
229 
236  template <class S>
237  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
238  internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
239  internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
240  if (a == 0) return b == 0;
241  if (b == 0) return false;
242  return *a == *b;
243  }
244 
245  template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator==(
246  const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
247  internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
248  internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
249  if (a == 0) return b == 0;
250  if (b == 0) return false;
251  return *a == *b;
252  }
253 
260  template <class S>
261  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
262  return !operator==(that);
263  }
264 
265  template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator!=(
266  const Persistent<S>& that) const {
267  return !operator==(that);
268  }

275  template <class S> V8_INLINE static Local<T> Cast(Local<S> that) {
276 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
277  // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
278  // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
279  if (that.IsEmpty()) return Local<T>();
280 #endif
281  return Local<T>(T::Cast(*that));
282  }
283 
289  template <class S>
290  V8_INLINE Local<S> As() const {
291  return Local<S>::Cast(*this);
292  }
293 
299  V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, Local<T> that);
300  V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate,
301  const PersistentBase<T>& that);
302 
303  private:
304  friend class Utils;
305  template<class F> friend class Eternal;
306  template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;
307  template<class F, class M> friend class Persistent;
308  template<class F> friend class Local;
309  template <class F>
310  friend class MaybeLocal;
311  template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
312  template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
313  friend class String;
314  friend class Object;
315  friend class Context;
316  friend class Private;
317  template<class F> friend class internal::CustomArguments;
318  friend Local<Primitive> Undefined(Isolate* isolate);
319  friend Local<Primitive> Null(Isolate* isolate);
320  friend Local<Boolean> True(Isolate* isolate);
321  friend Local<Boolean> False(Isolate* isolate);
322  friend class HandleScope;
323  friend class EscapableHandleScope;
324  template <class F1, class F2, class F3>
325  friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
326  template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;
327  template <class F>
328  friend class ReturnValue;

331  V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
332  T* val_;
333 };

364 
369  template <class S>
370  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool ToLocal(Local<S>* out) const {
371  out->val_ = IsEmpty() ? nullptr : this->val_;
372  return !IsEmpty();
373  }

415 static const int kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
416 static const int kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
417 
418 template <typename T>
419 class WeakCallbackInfo {
420  public:
421  typedef void (*Callback)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
422 
423  WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
424  void* embedder_fields[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback],
425  Callback* callback)
426  : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
427  for (int i = 0; i < kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
428  embedder_fields_[i] = embedder_fields[i];
429  }
430  }
431 
432  V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
433  V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
434  V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
435 
436  // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
437  // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
438  // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
439  // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
440  // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
441  // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
442  void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
443 
444  private:
445  Isolate* isolate_;
446  T* parameter_;
447  Callback* callback_;
448  void* embedder_fields_[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback];
449 };
450 
451 
452 // kParameter will pass a void* parameter back to the callback, kInternalFields
453 // will pass the first two internal fields back to the callback, kFinalizer
454 // will pass a void* parameter back, but is invoked before the object is
455 // actually collected, so it can be resurrected. In the last case, it is not
456 // possible to request a second pass callback.
457 enum class WeakCallbackType { kParameter, kInternalFields, kFinalizer };
458

633 template<class T>
634 class NonCopyablePersistentTraits {
635  public:
636  typedef Persistent<T, NonCopyablePersistentTraits<T> > NonCopyablePersistent;
637  static const bool kResetInDestructor = false;
638  template<class S, class M>
639  V8_INLINE static void Copy(const Persistent<S, M>& source,
640  NonCopyablePersistent* dest) {
641  Uncompilable<Object>();
642  }
643  // TODO(dcarney): come up with a good compile error here.
644  template<class O> V8_INLINE static void Uncompilable() {
645  TYPE_CHECK(O, Primitive);
646  }
647 };

657  static const bool kResetInDestructor = true;
658  template<class S, class M>
659  static V8_INLINE void Copy(const Persistent<S, M>& source,
660  CopyablePersistent* dest) {
661  // do nothing, just allow copy

674 template <class T, class M> class Persistent : public PersistentBase<T> {
675  public:
679  V8_INLINE Persistent() : PersistentBase<T>(0) { }
685  template <class S>
686  V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
687  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
688  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
689  }
695  template <class S, class M2>
696  V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, const Persistent<S, M2>& that)
697  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
698  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
699  }
706  V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
707  Copy(that);
708  }
709  template <class S, class M2>
710  V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
711  Copy(that);
712  }
713  V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent& that) { // NOLINT
714  Copy(that);
715  return *this;
716  }
717  template <class S, class M2>
718  V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) { // NOLINT
719  Copy(that);
720  return *this;
721  }
727  V8_INLINE ~Persistent() {
728  if (M::kResetInDestructor) this->Reset();
729  }
730 
731  // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
732  template <class S>
733  V8_INLINE static Persistent<T>& Cast(const Persistent<S>& that) { // NOLINT
734 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
735  // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
736  // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
737  if (!that.IsEmpty()) T::Cast(*that);
738 #endif
739  return reinterpret_cast<Persistent<T>&>(const_cast<Persistent<S>&>(that));
740  }
741 
742  // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
743  template <class S>
744  V8_INLINE Persistent<S>& As() const { // NOLINT
745  return Persistent<S>::Cast(*this);
746  }
747 
748  private:
749  friend class Isolate;
750  friend class Utils;
751  template<class F> friend class Local;
752  template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
753  template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
754 
755  explicit V8_INLINE Persistent(T* that) : PersistentBase<T>(that) {}
756  V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
757  template<class S, class M2>
758  V8_INLINE void Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that);
759 };

767 template <class T>
768 class Global : public PersistentBase<T> {
769  public:
773  V8_INLINE Global() : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {}
779  template <class S>
780  V8_INLINE Global(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
781  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
782  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
783  }
789  template <class S>
790  V8_INLINE Global(Isolate* isolate, const PersistentBase<S>& that)
791  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, that.val_)) {
792  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
793  }
797  V8_INLINE Global(Global&& other) : PersistentBase<T>(other.val_) { // NOLINT
798  other.val_ = nullptr;
799  }
800  V8_INLINE ~Global() { this->Reset(); }
804  template <class S>
805  V8_INLINE Global& operator=(Global<S>&& rhs) { // NOLINT
806  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
807  if (this != &rhs) {
808  this->Reset();
809  this->val_ = rhs.val_;
810  rhs.val_ = nullptr;
811  }
812  return *this;
813  }
817  Global Pass() { return static_cast<Global&&>(*this); } // NOLINT
818 
819  /*
820  * For compatibility with Chromium's base::Bind (base::Passed).
821  */
822  typedef void MoveOnlyTypeForCPP03;
823 
824  Global(const Global&) = delete;
825  void operator=(const Global&) = delete;
826 
827  private:
828  template <class F>
829  friend class ReturnValue;
830  V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
831 };

853 class V8_EXPORT HandleScope {

857  ~HandleScope();

864  V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const {
865  return reinterpret_cast<Isolate*>(isolate_);
866  }
867

869  void operator=(const HandleScope&) = delete;
870 
871  protected:
872  V8_INLINE HandleScope() {}
873 
874  void Initialize(Isolate* isolate);
875 
876  static internal::Object** CreateHandle(internal::Isolate* isolate,
877  internal::Object* value);
878 
879  private:
880  // Declaring operator new and delete as deleted is not spec compliant.
881  // Therefore declare them private instead to disable dynamic alloc
882  void* operator new(size_t size);
883  void* operator new[](size_t size);
884  void operator delete(void*, size_t);
885  void operator delete[](void*, size_t);
886

889  internal::Object* value);

894 
895  // Local::New uses CreateHandle with an Isolate* parameter.
896  template<class F> friend class Local;
897 
898  // Object::GetInternalField and Context::GetEmbedderData use CreateHandle with
899  // a HeapObject* in their shortcuts.
900  friend class Object;
901  friend class Context;
902 };

1012  Local<Primitive> Get(int index);
1013 };

1018 class ScriptOriginOptions {
1019  public:
1020  V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(bool is_shared_cross_origin = false,
1021  bool is_opaque = false, bool is_wasm = false,
1022  bool is_module = false)
1023  : flags_((is_shared_cross_origin ? kIsSharedCrossOrigin : 0) |
1024  (is_wasm ? kIsWasm : 0) | (is_opaque ? kIsOpaque : 0) |
1025  (is_module ? kIsModule : 0)) {}
1026  V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(int flags)
1027  : flags_(flags &
1028  (kIsSharedCrossOrigin | kIsOpaque | kIsWasm | kIsModule)) {}
1029 
1030  bool IsSharedCrossOrigin() const {
1031  return (flags_ & kIsSharedCrossOrigin) != 0;
1032  }
1033  bool IsOpaque() const { return (flags_ & kIsOpaque) != 0; }
1034  bool IsWasm() const { return (flags_ & kIsWasm) != 0; }
1035  bool IsModule() const { return (flags_ & kIsModule) != 0; }
1036 
1037  int Flags() const { return flags_; }
1038 
1039  private:
1040  enum {
1041  kIsSharedCrossOrigin = 1,
1042  kIsOpaque = 1 << 1,
1043  kIsWasm = 1 << 2,
1044  kIsModule = 1 << 3
1045  };
1046  const int flags_;
1047 };

1254 class V8_EXPORT ScriptCompiler {
1255  public:
1263  struct V8_EXPORT CachedData {
1264  enum BufferPolicy {
1265  BufferNotOwned,
1266  BufferOwned
1267  };
1268 
1269  CachedData()
1270  : data(NULL),
1271  length(0),
1272  rejected(false),
1273  buffer_policy(BufferNotOwned) {}
1274 
1275  // If buffer_policy is BufferNotOwned, the caller keeps the ownership of
1276  // data and guarantees that it stays alive until the CachedData object is
1277  // destroyed. If the policy is BufferOwned, the given data will be deleted
1278  // (with delete[]) when the CachedData object is destroyed.
1279  CachedData(const uint8_t* data, int length,
1280  BufferPolicy buffer_policy = BufferNotOwned);
1281  ~CachedData();
1282  // TODO(marja): Async compilation; add constructors which take a callback
1283  // which will be called when V8 no longer needs the data.
1284  const uint8_t* data;
1285  int length;
1286  bool rejected;
1287  BufferPolicy buffer_policy;
1288 
1289  // Prevent copying.
1290  CachedData(const CachedData&) = delete;
1291  CachedData& operator=(const CachedData&) = delete;
1292  };
1293 
1297  class Source {
1298  public:
1299  // Source takes ownership of CachedData.
1300  V8_INLINE Source(Local<String> source_string, const ScriptOrigin& origin,
1301  CachedData* cached_data = NULL);
1302  V8_INLINE Source(Local<String> source_string,
1303  CachedData* cached_data = NULL);
1304  V8_INLINE ~Source();
1305 
1306  // Ownership of the CachedData or its buffers is *not* transferred to the
1307  // caller. The CachedData object is alive as long as the Source object is
1308  // alive.
1309  V8_INLINE const CachedData* GetCachedData() const;
1310 
1311  V8_INLINE const ScriptOriginOptions& GetResourceOptions() const;
1312 
1313  // Prevent copying.
1314  Source(const Source&) = delete;
1315  Source& operator=(const Source&) = delete;
1316 
1317  private:
1318  friend class ScriptCompiler;
1319 
1320  Local<String> source_string;
1321 
1322  // Origin information
1323  Local<Value> resource_name;
1324  Local<Integer> resource_line_offset;
1325  Local<Integer> resource_column_offset;
1326  ScriptOriginOptions resource_options;
1327  Local<Value> source_map_url;
1328  Local<PrimitiveArray> host_defined_options;
1329 
1330  // Cached data from previous compilation (if a kConsume*Cache flag is
1331  // set), or hold newly generated cache data (kProduce*Cache flags) are
1332  // set when calling a compile method.
1333  CachedData* cached_data;
1334  };

3115  // Implements CreateDataProperty (ECMA-262, 7.3.4).
3116  //
3117  // Defines a configurable, writable, enumerable property with the given value
3118  // on the object unless the property already exists and is not configurable
3119  // or the object is not extensible.
3120  //
3121  // Returns true on success.
3122  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT Maybe<bool> CreateDataProperty(Local<Context> context,
3123  Local<Name> key,

3126  uint32_t index,

3129  // Implements DefineOwnProperty.
3130  //
3131  // In general, CreateDataProperty will be faster, however, does not allow
3132  // for specifying attributes.
3133  //
3134  // Returns true on success.
3135  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT Maybe<bool> DefineOwnProperty(
3136  Local<Context> context, Local<Name> key, Local<Value> value,
3137  PropertyAttribute attributes = None);
3138 
3139  // Implements Object.DefineProperty(O, P, Attributes), see Ecma-262 19.1.2.4.
3140  //
3141  // The defineProperty function is used to add an own property or
3142  // update the attributes of an existing own property of an object.
3143  //
3144  // Both data and accessor descriptors can be used.
3145  //
3146  // In general, CreateDataProperty is faster, however, does not allow
3147  // for specifying attributes or an accessor descriptor.
3148  //
3149  // The PropertyDescriptor can change when redefining a property.
3150  //
3151  // Returns true on success.
3152  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT Maybe<bool> DefineProperty(
3153  Local<Context> context, Local<Name> key, PropertyDescriptor& descriptor);
3154 
3155  // Sets an own property on this object bypassing interceptors and
3156  // overriding accessors or read-only properties.
3157  //
3158  // Note that if the object has an interceptor the property will be set
3159  // locally, but since the interceptor takes precedence the local property
3160  // will only be returned if the interceptor doesn't return a value.
3161  //
3162  // Note also that this only works for named properties.
3163  V8_DEPRECATED("Use CreateDataProperty / DefineOwnProperty",
3164  Maybe<bool> ForceSet(Local<Context> context, Local<Value> key,
3165  Local<Value> value,
3166  PropertyAttribute attribs = None));

3647 template<typename T>
3648 class ReturnValue {
3649  public:
3650  template <class S> V8_INLINE ReturnValue(const ReturnValue<S>& that)
3651  : value_(that.value_) {
3652  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
3653  }
3654  // Local setters
3655  template <typename S>
3656  V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("Use Global<> instead",
3657  void Set(const Persistent<S>& handle));
3658  template <typename S>
3659  V8_INLINE void Set(const Global<S>& handle);
3660  template <typename S>
3661  V8_INLINE void Set(const Local<S> handle);
3662  // Fast primitive setters
3663  V8_INLINE void Set(bool value);
3664  V8_INLINE void Set(double i);
3665  V8_INLINE void Set(int32_t i);
3666  V8_INLINE void Set(uint32_t i);
3667  // Fast JS primitive setters
3668  V8_INLINE void SetNull();
3669  V8_INLINE void SetUndefined();
3670  V8_INLINE void SetEmptyString();
3671  // Convenience getter for Isolate
3672  V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const;
3673 
3674  // Pointer setter: Uncompilable to prevent inadvertent misuse.
3675  template <typename S>
3676  V8_INLINE void Set(S* whatever);
3677 
3678  // Getter. Creates a new Local<> so it comes with a certain performance
3679  // hit. If the ReturnValue was not yet set, this will return the undefined
3680  // value.
3681  V8_INLINE Local<Value> Get() const;
3682 
3683  private:
3684  template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
3685  template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
3686  template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
3687  template <class F, class G, class H>
3688  friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
3689  V8_INLINE void SetInternal(internal::Object* value) { *value_ = value; }
3690  V8_INLINE internal::Object* GetDefaultValue();
3691  V8_INLINE explicit ReturnValue(internal::Object** slot);
3692  internal::Object** value_;
3693 };

4155 // TODO(mtrofin): rename WasmCompiledModule to WasmModuleObject, for
4156 // consistency with internal APIs.
4157 class V8_EXPORT WasmCompiledModule : public Object {
4158  public:
4159  typedef std::pair<std::unique_ptr<const uint8_t[]>, size_t> SerializedModule;
4160  // A buffer that is owned by the caller.
4161  typedef std::pair<const uint8_t*, size_t> CallerOwnedBuffer;
4162 
4163  // An opaque, native heap object for transferring wasm modules. It
4164  // supports move semantics, and does not support copy semantics.
4165  class TransferrableModule final {
4166  public:
4167  TransferrableModule(TransferrableModule&& src) = default;
4168  TransferrableModule(const TransferrableModule& src) = delete;
4169 
4170  TransferrableModule& operator=(TransferrableModule&& src) = default;
4171  TransferrableModule& operator=(const TransferrableModule& src) = delete;
4172 
4173  private:
4174  typedef std::pair<std::unique_ptr<const uint8_t[]>, size_t> OwnedBuffer;
4175  friend class WasmCompiledModule;
4176  TransferrableModule(OwnedBuffer&& code, OwnedBuffer&& bytes)
4177  : compiled_code(std::move(code)), wire_bytes(std::move(bytes)) {}
4178 
4179  OwnedBuffer compiled_code = {nullptr, 0};
4180  OwnedBuffer wire_bytes = {nullptr, 0};
4181  };
4182 
4183  // Get an in-memory, non-persistable, and context-independent (meaning,
4184  // suitable for transfer to another Isolate and Context) representation
4185  // of this wasm compiled module.
4186  TransferrableModule GetTransferrableModule();
4187 
4188  // Efficiently re-create a WasmCompiledModule, without recompiling, from
4189  // a TransferrableModule.
4190  static MaybeLocal<WasmCompiledModule> FromTransferrableModule(
4191  Isolate* isolate, const TransferrableModule&);
4192 
4193  // Get the wasm-encoded bytes that were used to compile this module.
4194  Local<String> GetWasmWireBytes();
4195 
4196  // Serialize the compiled module. The serialized data does not include the
4197  // uncompiled bytes.
4198  SerializedModule Serialize();
4199 
4200  // If possible, deserialize the module, otherwise compile it from the provided
4201  // uncompiled bytes.
4202  static MaybeLocal<WasmCompiledModule> DeserializeOrCompile(
4203  Isolate* isolate, const CallerOwnedBuffer& serialized_module,
4204  const CallerOwnedBuffer& wire_bytes);
4205  V8_INLINE static WasmCompiledModule* Cast(Value* obj);
4206 
4207  private:
4208  // TODO(ahaas): please remove the friend once streamed compilation is
4209  // implemented
4210  friend class WasmModuleObjectBuilder;
4211 
4212  static MaybeLocal<WasmCompiledModule> Deserialize(
4213  Isolate* isolate, const CallerOwnedBuffer& serialized_module,
4214  const CallerOwnedBuffer& wire_bytes);
4215  static MaybeLocal<WasmCompiledModule> Compile(Isolate* isolate,
4216  const uint8_t* start,
4217  size_t length);
4218  static CallerOwnedBuffer AsCallerOwned(
4219  const TransferrableModule::OwnedBuffer& buff) {
4220  return {buff.first.get(), buff.second};
4221  }
4222 
4223  WasmCompiledModule();
4224  static void CheckCast(Value* obj);
4225 };

5675 struct NamedPropertyHandlerConfiguration {
5676  NamedPropertyHandlerConfiguration(
5678  GenericNamedPropertyGetterCallback getter = 0,
5679  GenericNamedPropertySetterCallback setter = 0,
5680  GenericNamedPropertyQueryCallback query = 0,
5681  GenericNamedPropertyDeleterCallback deleter = 0,
5682  GenericNamedPropertyEnumeratorCallback enumerator = 0,
5683  Local<Value> data = Local<Value>(),
5684  PropertyHandlerFlags flags = PropertyHandlerFlags::kNone)
5685  : getter(getter),
5686  setter(setter),
5687  query(query),
5688  deleter(deleter),
5689  enumerator(enumerator),
5690  definer(0),
5691  descriptor(0),
5692  data(data),
5693  flags(flags) {}
5694 
5695  NamedPropertyHandlerConfiguration(
5696  GenericNamedPropertyGetterCallback getter,
5697  GenericNamedPropertySetterCallback setter,
5698  GenericNamedPropertyDescriptorCallback descriptor,
5699  GenericNamedPropertyDeleterCallback deleter,
5700  GenericNamedPropertyEnumeratorCallback enumerator,
5701  GenericNamedPropertyDefinerCallback definer,
5702  Local<Value> data = Local<Value>(),
5703  PropertyHandlerFlags flags = PropertyHandlerFlags::kNone)
5704  : getter(getter),
5705  setter(setter),
5706  query(0),
5707  deleter(deleter),
5708  enumerator(enumerator),
5709  definer(definer),
5710  descriptor(descriptor),
5711  data(data),
5712  flags(flags) {}
5713 
5714  GenericNamedPropertyGetterCallback getter;
5715  GenericNamedPropertySetterCallback setter;
5716  GenericNamedPropertyQueryCallback query;
5717  GenericNamedPropertyDeleterCallback deleter;
5718  GenericNamedPropertyEnumeratorCallback enumerator;
5719  GenericNamedPropertyDefinerCallback definer;
5720  GenericNamedPropertyDescriptorCallback descriptor;
5721  Local<Value> data;
5722  PropertyHandlerFlags flags;
5723 };

6594 struct JitCodeEvent {
6595  enum EventType {
6596  CODE_ADDED,
6597  CODE_MOVED,
6598  CODE_REMOVED,
6599  CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO,
6600  CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING,
6601  CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING
6602  };
6603  // Definition of the code position type. The "POSITION" type means the place
6604  // in the source code which are of interest when making stack traces to
6605  // pin-point the source location of a stack frame as close as possible.
6606  // The "STATEMENT_POSITION" means the place at the beginning of each
6607  // statement, and is used to indicate possible break locations.
6608  enum PositionType { POSITION, STATEMENT_POSITION };
6609 
6610  // Type of event.
6611  EventType type;
6612  // Start of the instructions.
6613  void* code_start;
6614  // Size of the instructions.
6615  size_t code_len;
6616  // Script info for CODE_ADDED event.
6617  Local<UnboundScript> script;
6618  // User-defined data for *_LINE_INFO_* event. It's used to hold the source
6619  // code line information which is returned from the
6620  // CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING event. And it's passed to subsequent
6621  // CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO and CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING events.
6622  void* user_data;
6623 
6624  struct name_t {
6625  // Name of the object associated with the code, note that the string is not
6626  // zero-terminated.
6627  const char* str;
6628  // Number of chars in str.
6629  size_t len;
6630  };
6631 
6632  struct line_info_t {
6633  // PC offset
6634  size_t offset;
6635  // Code position
6636  size_t pos;
6637  // The position type.
6638  PositionType position_type;
6639  };
6640 
6641  union {
6642  // Only valid for CODE_ADDED.
6643  struct name_t name;
6644 
6645  // Only valid for CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO
6646  struct line_info_t line_info;
6647 
6648  // New location of instructions. Only valid for CODE_MOVED.
6649  void* new_code_start;
6650  };
6651 };
6652 
6658 enum RAILMode {
6659  // Response performance mode: In this mode very low virtual machine latency
6660  // is provided. V8 will try to avoid JavaScript execution interruptions.
6661  // Throughput may be throttled.
6662  PERFORMANCE_RESPONSE,
6663  // Animation performance mode: In this mode low virtual machine latency is
6664  // provided. V8 will try to avoid as many JavaScript execution interruptions
6665  // as possible. Throughput may be throttled. This is the default mode.
6666  PERFORMANCE_ANIMATION,
6667  // Idle performance mode: The embedder is idle. V8 can complete deferred work
6668  // in this mode.
6669  PERFORMANCE_IDLE,
6670  // Load performance mode: In this mode high throughput is provided. V8 may
6671  // turn off latency optimizations.
6672  PERFORMANCE_LOAD
6673 };
6674

6679  kJitCodeEventDefault = 0,
6680  // Generate callbacks for already existent code.
6681  kJitCodeEventEnumExisting = 1

6806 struct SerializeInternalFieldsCallback {
6807  typedef StartupData (*CallbackFunction)(Local<Object> holder, int index,
6808  void* data);
6809  SerializeInternalFieldsCallback(CallbackFunction function = nullptr,
6810  void* data_arg = nullptr)
6811  : callback(function), data(data_arg) {}
6812  CallbackFunction callback;
6813  void* data;
6814 };
6815 // Note that these fields are called "internal fields" in the API and called
6816 // "embedder fields" within V8.
6817 typedef SerializeInternalFieldsCallback SerializeEmbedderFieldsCallback;
6818 
6823 struct DeserializeInternalFieldsCallback {
6824  typedef void (*CallbackFunction)(Local<Object> holder, int index,
6825  StartupData payload, void* data);
6826  DeserializeInternalFieldsCallback(CallbackFunction function = nullptr,
6827  void* data_arg = nullptr)
6828  : callback(function), data(data_arg) {}
6829  void (*callback)(Local<Object> holder, int index, StartupData payload,
6830  void* data);
6831  void* data;
6832 };
6833 typedef DeserializeInternalFieldsCallback DeserializeEmbedderFieldsCallback;

8273 
8284 template <class T>
8285 class Maybe {
8286  public:
8287  V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value_; }
8288  V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value_; }
8289 
8293  V8_INLINE T ToChecked() const { return FromJust(); }
8294 
8299  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool To(T* out) const {
8300  if (V8_LIKELY(IsJust())) *out = value_;
8301  return IsJust();
8302  }
8303 
8308  V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
8309  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
8310  return value_;
8311  }
8312 
8317  V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
8318  return has_value_ ? value_ : default_value;
8319  }
8320 
8321  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
8322  return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
8323  (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
8324  }
8325 
8326  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
8327  return !operator==(other);
8328  }
8329 
8330  private:
8331  Maybe() : has_value_(false) {}
8332  explicit Maybe(const T& t) : has_value_(true), value_(t) {}
8333 
8334  bool has_value_;
8335  T value_;
8336 
8337  template <class U>
8338  friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
8339  template <class U>
8340  friend Maybe<U> Just(const U& u);
8341 };
8342 
8343 template <class T>
8344 inline Maybe<T> Nothing() {
8345  return Maybe<T>();
8346 }
8347 
8348 template <class T>
8349 inline Maybe<T> Just(const T& t) {
8350  return Maybe<T>(t);
8351 }

8353 // A template specialization of Maybe<T> for the case of T = void.
8354 template <>
8355 class Maybe<void> {
8356  public:
8357  V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !is_valid_; }
8358  V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return is_valid_; }
8359 
8360  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
8361  return IsJust() == other.IsJust();
8362  }
8363 
8364  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
8365  return !operator==(other);
8366  }
8367 
8368  private:
8369  struct JustTag {};
8370 
8371  Maybe() : is_valid_(false) {}
8372  explicit Maybe(JustTag) : is_valid_(true) {}
8373 
8374  bool is_valid_;
8375 
8376  template <class U>
8377  friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
8378  friend Maybe<void> JustVoid();
8379 };
8380 
8381 inline Maybe<void> JustVoid() { return Maybe<void>(Maybe<void>::JustTag()); }

8946 const int kApiPointerSize = sizeof(void*); // NOLINT
8947 const int kApiIntSize = sizeof(int); // NOLINT
8948 const int kApiInt64Size = sizeof(int64_t); // NOLINT
8949 
8950 // Tag information for HeapObject.
8951 const int kHeapObjectTag = 1;
8952 const int kHeapObjectTagSize = 2;
8953 const intptr_t kHeapObjectTagMask = (1 << kHeapObjectTagSize) - 1;
8954 
8955 // Tag information for Smi.
8956 const int kSmiTag = 0;
8957 const int kSmiTagSize = 1;
8958 const intptr_t kSmiTagMask = (1 << kSmiTagSize) - 1;
8959 
8960 template <size_t ptr_size> struct SmiTagging;
8961 
8962 template<int kSmiShiftSize>
8963 V8_INLINE internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
8964  int smi_shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
8965  uintptr_t tagged_value =
8966  (static_cast<uintptr_t>(value) << smi_shift_bits) | kSmiTag;
8967  return reinterpret_cast<internal::Object*>(tagged_value);
8968 }
8969 
8970 // Smi constants for 32-bit systems.
8971 template <> struct SmiTagging<4> {
8972  enum { kSmiShiftSize = 0, kSmiValueSize = 31 };
8973  static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
8974  static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
8975  V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
8976  int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
8977  // Throw away top 32 bits and shift down (requires >> to be sign extending).
8978  return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value)) >> shift_bits;
8979  }
8980  V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
8981  return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
8982  }
8983  V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
8984  // To be representable as an tagged small integer, the two
8985  // most-significant bits of 'value' must be either 00 or 11 due to
8986  // sign-extension. To check this we add 01 to the two
8987  // most-significant bits, and check if the most-significant bit is 0
8988  //
8989  // CAUTION: The original code below:
8990  // bool result = ((value + 0x40000000) & 0x80000000) == 0;
8991  // may lead to incorrect results according to the C language spec, and
8992  // in fact doesn't work correctly with gcc4.1.1 in some cases: The
8993  // compiler may produce undefined results in case of signed integer
8994  // overflow. The computation must be done w/ unsigned ints.
8995  return static_cast<uintptr_t>(value + 0x40000000U) < 0x80000000U;
8996  }
8997 };
8998 
8999 // Smi constants for 64-bit systems.
9000 template <> struct SmiTagging<8> {
9001  enum { kSmiShiftSize = 31, kSmiValueSize = 32 };
9002  static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
9003  static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
9004  V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
9005  int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
9006  // Shift down and throw away top 32 bits.
9007  return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value) >> shift_bits);
9008  }
9009  V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
9010  return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
9011  }
9012  V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
9013  // To be representable as a long smi, the value must be a 32-bit integer.
9014  return (value == static_cast<int32_t>(value));
9015  }
9016 };
9017 
9018 typedef SmiTagging<kApiPointerSize> PlatformSmiTagging;
9019 const int kSmiShiftSize = PlatformSmiTagging::kSmiShiftSize;
9020 const int kSmiValueSize = PlatformSmiTagging::kSmiValueSize;
9021 V8_INLINE static bool SmiValuesAre31Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 31; }
9022 V8_INLINE static bool SmiValuesAre32Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 32; }

9111  return ReadField<uint16_t>(map, kMapInstanceTypeOffset);
9112  }

9119  V8_INLINE static bool IsExternalTwoByteString(int instance_type) {

9124  V8_INLINE static uint8_t GetNodeFlag(internal::Object** obj, int shift) {
9125  uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
9126  return *addr & static_cast<uint8_t>(1U << shift);
9127  }
9128 
9129  V8_INLINE static void UpdateNodeFlag(internal::Object** obj,
9130  bool value, int shift) {
9131  uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
9132  uint8_t mask = static_cast<uint8_t>(1U << shift);
9133  *addr = static_cast<uint8_t>((*addr & ~mask) | (value << shift));
9134  }
9135 
9136  V8_INLINE static uint8_t GetNodeState(internal::Object** obj) {
9137  uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
9138  return *addr & kNodeStateMask;
9139  }
9140 
9141  V8_INLINE static void UpdateNodeState(internal::Object** obj,
9142  uint8_t value) {
9143  uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
9144  *addr = static_cast<uint8_t>((*addr & ~kNodeStateMask) | value);
9145  }

9147  V8_INLINE static void SetEmbedderData(v8::Isolate* isolate,
9148  uint32_t slot,
9149  void* data) {
9150  uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(isolate) +
9151  kIsolateEmbedderDataOffset + slot * kApiPointerSize;
9152  *reinterpret_cast<void**>(addr) = data;
9153  }
9154 
9155  V8_INLINE static void* GetEmbedderData(const v8::Isolate* isolate,
9156  uint32_t slot) {
9157  const uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(isolate) +
9158  kIsolateEmbedderDataOffset + slot * kApiPointerSize;
9159  return *reinterpret_cast<void* const*>(addr);
9160  }
9161 
9162  V8_INLINE static internal::Object** GetRoot(v8::Isolate* isolate,
9163  int index) {

9165  return reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(addr + index * kApiPointerSize);

9167 
9168  template <typename T>
9169  V8_INLINE static T ReadField(const internal::Object* ptr, int offset) {
9170  const uint8_t* addr =
9171  reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(ptr) + offset - kHeapObjectTag;
9172  return *reinterpret_cast<const T*>(addr);
9173  }
9174 
9175  template <typename T>
9176  V8_INLINE static T ReadEmbedderData(const v8::Context* context, int index) {
9177  typedef internal::Object O;
9178  typedef internal::Internals I;
9179  O* ctx = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(context);
9180  int embedder_data_offset = I::kContextHeaderSize +
9181  (internal::kApiPointerSize * I::kContextEmbedderDataIndex);
9182  O* embedder_data = I::ReadField<O*>(ctx, embedder_data_offset);
9183  int value_offset =
9184  I::kFixedArrayHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
9185  return I::ReadField<T>(embedder_data, value_offset);
9186  }
9187 };

9257 template <class T, class M>
9258 template <class S, class M2>
9259 void Persistent<T, M>::Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) {
9260  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
9261  this->Reset();
9262  if (that.IsEmpty()) return;
9263  internal::Object** p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
9264  this->val_ = reinterpret_cast<T*>(V8::CopyPersistent(p));
9265  M::Copy(that, this);
9266 }

9268 template <class T>
9269 bool PersistentBase<T>::IsIndependent() const {
9270  return true;
9271 }
9272 
9273 template <class T>
9274 bool PersistentBase<T>::IsNearDeath() const {
9275  typedef internal::Internals I;
9276  if (this->IsEmpty()) return false;
9277  uint8_t node_state =
9278  I::GetNodeState(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_));
9279  return node_state == I::kNodeStateIsNearDeathValue ||
9280  node_state == I::kNodeStateIsPendingValue;
9281 }
9282 
9283 
9284 template <class T>
9285 bool PersistentBase<T>::IsWeak() const {
9286  typedef internal::Internals I;
9287  if (this->IsEmpty()) return false;
9288  return I::GetNodeState(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_)) ==
9289  I::kNodeStateIsWeakValue;
9290 }

9293 template <class T>
9294 void PersistentBase<T>::Reset() {
9295  if (this->IsEmpty()) return;
9296  V8::DisposeGlobal(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_));
9297  val_ = 0;
9298 }

9322 template <class T>
9323 template <typename P>
9324 V8_INLINE void PersistentBase<T>::SetWeak(
9325  P* parameter, typename WeakCallbackInfo<P>::Callback callback,
9326  WeakCallbackType type) {
9327  typedef typename WeakCallbackInfo<void>::Callback Callback;
9328  V8::MakeWeak(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_), parameter,
9329  reinterpret_cast<Callback>(callback), type);
9330 }
9331 
9332 template <class T>

9334  V8::MakeWeak(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object***>(&this->val_));
9335 }

9341  V8::ClearWeak(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_)));

9369  uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + I::kNodeClassIdOffset;
9370  *reinterpret_cast<uint16_t*>(addr) = class_id;

9426 template<typename T>
9427 void ReturnValue<T>::Set(int32_t i) {
9428  TYPE_CHECK(T, Integer);
9429  typedef internal::Internals I;
9430  if (V8_LIKELY(I::IsValidSmi(i))) {
9431  *value_ = I::IntToSmi(i);
9432  return;
9433  }
9434  Set(Integer::New(GetIsolate(), i));
9435 }
9436 
9437 template<typename T>
9438 void ReturnValue<T>::Set(uint32_t i) {
9439  TYPE_CHECK(T, Integer);
9440  // Can't simply use INT32_MAX here for whatever reason.
9441  bool fits_into_int32_t = (i & (1U << 31)) == 0;
9442  if (V8_LIKELY(fits_into_int32_t)) {
9443  Set(static_cast<int32_t>(i));
9444  return;
9445  }
9446  Set(Integer::NewFromUnsigned(GetIsolate(), i));
9447 }
9448 
9449 template<typename T>
9450 void ReturnValue<T>::Set(bool value) {
9451  TYPE_CHECK(T, Boolean);
9452  typedef internal::Internals I;
9453  int root_index;
9454  if (value) {
9455  root_index = I::kTrueValueRootIndex;
9456  } else {
9457  root_index = I::kFalseValueRootIndex;
9458  }
9459  *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), root_index);
9460 }

9467 }

9489 template <typename T>
9490 Local<Value> ReturnValue<T>::Get() const {
9491  typedef internal::Internals I;
9492  if (*value_ == *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kTheHoleValueRootIndex))
9493  return Local<Value>(*Undefined(GetIsolate()));
9494  return Local<Value>::New(GetIsolate(), reinterpret_cast<Value*>(value_));
9495 }

9502 }

9652 
9653 Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
9654 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9655  typedef internal::Object O;
9656  typedef internal::HeapObject HO;
9657  typedef internal::Internals I;
9658  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
9659  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
9660  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
9661  auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
9662  if (instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
9663  instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||
9664  instance_type == I::kJSSpecialApiObjectType) {
9665  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
9666  O* value = I::ReadField<O*>(obj, offset);
9667  O** result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(reinterpret_cast<HO*>(obj), value);
9668  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
9669  }
9670 #endif
9671  return SlowGetInternalField(index);
9672 }
9673 
9674 
9675 void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
9676 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9677  typedef internal::Object O;
9678  typedef internal::Internals I;
9679  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
9680  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
9681  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
9682  auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
9683  if (V8_LIKELY(instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
9684  instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||
9685  instance_type == I::kJSSpecialApiObjectType)) {
9686  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
9687  return I::ReadField<void*>(obj, offset);
9688  }
9689 #endif
9690  return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
9691 }

9710 String::ExternalStringResource* String::GetExternalStringResource() const {
9711  typedef internal::Object O;
9712  typedef internal::Internals I;
9713  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
9714  String::ExternalStringResource* result;
9715  if (I::IsExternalTwoByteString(I::GetInstanceType(obj))) {
9716  void* value = I::ReadField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
9717  result = reinterpret_cast<String::ExternalStringResource*>(value);
9718  } else {
9719  result = NULL;
9720  }
9721 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9722  VerifyExternalStringResource(result);
9723 #endif
9724  return result;
9725 }
9726 
9727 
9728 String::ExternalStringResourceBase* String::GetExternalStringResourceBase(
9729  String::Encoding* encoding_out) const {
9730  typedef internal::Object O;
9731  typedef internal::Internals I;
9732  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
9733  int type = I::GetInstanceType(obj) & I::kFullStringRepresentationMask;
9734  *encoding_out = static_cast<Encoding>(type & I::kStringEncodingMask);
9735  ExternalStringResourceBase* resource = NULL;
9736  if (type == I::kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag ||
9737  type == I::kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag) {
9738  void* value = I::ReadField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
9739  resource = static_cast<ExternalStringResourceBase*>(value);
9740  }
9741 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9742  VerifyExternalStringResourceBase(resource, *encoding_out);
9743 #endif
9744  return resource;
9745 }

9756 bool Value::QuickIsUndefined() const {

9758  typedef internal::Internals I;
9759  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
9760  if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
9761  if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
9762  return (I::GetOddballKind(obj) == I::kUndefinedOddballKind);
9763 }

10254 
10255 int64_t Isolate::AdjustAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemory(
10256  int64_t change_in_bytes) {
10257  typedef internal::Internals I;
10258  const int64_t kMemoryReducerActivationLimit = 32 * 1024 * 1024;
10259  int64_t* external_memory = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
10260  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryOffset);
10261  int64_t* external_memory_limit = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
10262  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryLimitOffset);
10263  int64_t* external_memory_at_last_mc =
10264  reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) +
10265  I::kExternalMemoryAtLastMarkCompactOffset);
10266  const int64_t amount = *external_memory + change_in_bytes;
10267 
10268  *external_memory = amount;
10269 
10270  int64_t allocation_diff_since_last_mc =
10271  *external_memory_at_last_mc - *external_memory;
10272  allocation_diff_since_last_mc = allocation_diff_since_last_mc < 0
10273  ? -allocation_diff_since_last_mc
10274  : allocation_diff_since_last_mc;
10275  if (allocation_diff_since_last_mc > kMemoryReducerActivationLimit) {
10276  CheckMemoryPressure();
10277  }
10278 
10279  if (change_in_bytes < 0) {
10280  *external_memory_limit += change_in_bytes;
10281  }
10282 
10283  if (change_in_bytes > 0 && amount > *external_memory_limit) {
10284  ReportExternalAllocationLimitReached();
10285  }
10286  return *external_memory;
10287 }
10288 
10289 Local<Value> Context::GetEmbedderData(int index) {
10290 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
10291  typedef internal::Object O;
10292  typedef internal::HeapObject HO;
10293  typedef internal::Internals I;
10294  HO* context = *reinterpret_cast<HO**>(this);
10295  O** result =
10296  HandleScope::CreateHandle(context, I::ReadEmbedderData<O*>(this, index));
10297  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
10298 #else
10299  return SlowGetEmbedderData(index);
10300 #endif
10301 }
